Troika Hires JPMorgan’s Malkov as Equity Capital Director

-- B y   A l e x   N i c h o l s o n
-- 
2011-08-24T17:08:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-24/troika-hires-jpmorgan-s-malkov-as-equity-capital-markets-head.html
Troika Dialog, Russia’s oldest
investment bank, hired  JPMorgan Chase & Co. (JPM) ’s Anton Malkov as a
director for  equity capital markets .  Malkov, previously an executive director at JPMorgan, will
work on equity fundraising and structuring deals, the Moscow-
based brokerage said in an e-mailed statement today.  Troika Dialog, which is being acquired by Russia’s largest
lender, OAO Sberbank, added three other bankers this month.
Chris Weafer was hired as chief strategist after just a month in
a similar role at ING Groep NV. Olga Klimov came from UBS AG in
New York as global head of equity sales based in Moscow and
James Corrigan joined from VTB Capital for an investment-banking
role.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Nicholson in Moscow at 
